  "prompt": "Is it true that we fantasize about friends of opposite gender?",
  "response": "It's important to note that human behavior and experiences are diverse and nuanced. Research indicates that people can and do experience a wide range of thoughts and fantasies, including those involving friends of the opposite gender. Fantasizing can be influenced by numerous factors such as individual personality, sexual orientation, level of intimacy, and the nature of the friendship. \n\nIt is not universally true for everyone, as people are different in their desires and levels of attraction to others. For some, friendships with the opposite gender remain strictly platonic with no sexual or romantic fantasies involved, while for others, it may include such thoughts. Fantasies are a normal part of human psychology and can vary greatly from person to person.",
